.TH phoenixdkim2-verify 1 "PhoenixDKIM"
.SH NAME
.B phoenixdkim2-verify
\- DKIM2 chain verifier (test tool)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B phoenixdkim2-verify
[\-\-mail\-from "<a@b>"]
[\-\-rcpt\-to "<c@d>"]...
[\-\-ignore\-timestamps]
[\-\-dns\-fixture FILE]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B phoenixdkim2-verify
reads a message on standard input and verifies its experimental DKIM2 chain
(draft\-ietf\-dkim\-dkim2\-spec): the signature chain, the envelope binding, and
the body and header hashes.  When the message carries more than one
.I Message\-Instance
it also walks the chain backward, reconstructing each prior instance from the
modifying instance's recipe and re\-checking that instance's hashes
.RI ( DKIM2\-extended ).
The verdict is printed to standard output and reflected in the exit status.
.PP
It exists to exercise the chain against interop fixtures without an MTA; the
milter
.RI ( phoenixdkim (8),
.I DKIM2Mode )
is the production verification path.  Built only when PhoenixDKIM is compiled
with experimental DKIM2 support
.RI ( WITH_DKIM2 ).
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.I \-\-mail\-from "<a@b>"
The live SMTP reverse\-path to check against the top signature's
.IR mf= .
.TP
.I \-\-rcpt\-to "<c@d>"
A live SMTP forward\-path to check against the top signature's
.IR rt= .
May be repeated.
.TP
.I \-\-ignore\-timestamps
Skip the signature\-age (14\-day) check.
.TP
.I \-\-dns\-fixture FILE
Resolve public keys from a fixture file of
.I "qname<WSP>TXT\-record"
lines instead of live DNS, making a chain verifiable offline.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
PASS \- the chain verified.
.TP
.B 1
FAIL \- a hash or signature did not match.
.TP
.B 2
PERMERROR \- malformed, missing, or otherwise unrecoverable.
.TP
.B 3
TEMPERROR \- a transient failure (for example, a key could not be fetched).
.TP
.B 4
NONE \- no
.I DKIM2\-Signature
was present.
.SH SEE ALSO
.I phoenixdkim2-sign (1),
.I phoenixdkim (8),
.I phoenixdkim.conf (5)
